---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Palchat tech stack">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="app-container">
      <header style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">About · Tech stack</p>
        <h1 class="section-title" style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: var(--sp-2);">
          The stack behind Palchat.
        </h1>
        <p class="body-text" style="max-width: 640px; margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          A simple, modern setup focused on fast pages, small interactive tools, and boring-but-reliable infra.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="section-tight" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
        <h2 class="section-eyebrow">High-level view</h2>
        <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3); display: grid; gap: var(--sp-4);">
        <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="section-eyebrow">Frontend</p>
            <p class="body-text-small">
              <span style="font-weight: 500;">Astro + React + Tailwind</span> — mostly static pages with small interactive React islands.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="section-eyebrow">Backend</p>
            <p class="body-text-small">
              <span style="font-weight: 500;">Serverless functions + Postgres</span> — lightweight APIs backed by a single relational database.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="section-eyebrow">Infra</p>
            <p class="body-text-small">
              <span style="font-weight: 500;">Vercel + managed Postgres</span> — zero-maintenance hosting with SSL, CI, and database integrations.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section-tight" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
        <h2 class="section-eyebrow">Stack by layer</h2>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--sp-5);">
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="section-title" style="font-size: 1rem;">
              Presentation &amp; UI
            </h3>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-emerald-500/50 bg-emerald-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-emerald-200">
              Astro (site framework)
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-sky-500/50 bg-sky-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-sky-200">
              React (interactive islands)
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/50 bg-indigo-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-indigo-200">
              Tailwind CSS (design system)
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
            Pages are mostly static for speed; React is only used where interactivity is needed (like the thoughts demo and future tools).
          </p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-top: var(--sp-4);">
            <h3 class="section-title" style="font-size: 1rem;">
              APIs &amp; logic
            </h3>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-500/50 bg-amber-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-amber-200">
              Vercel Serverless Functions
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-500/50 bg-slate-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Node.js runtime
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-fuchsia-500/50 bg-fuchsia-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-fuchsia-200">
              Nodemailer (transactional email)
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
            Small, single-purpose functions are used for database-backed features and contact flows.
          </p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-top: var(--sp-4);">
            <h3 class="section-title" style="font-size: 1rem;">
              Data &amp; storage
            </h3>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-cyan-500/50 bg-cyan-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-cyan-200">
              PostgreSQL
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-teal-500/50 bg-teal-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-teal-200">
              Pooled client (`pg`)
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-rose-500/50 bg-rose-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-rose-200">
              Neon / any Postgres
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
            A single relational database stores thoughts, user accounts, sessions, tools, and future idea-related data.
          </p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-top: var(--sp-4);">
            <h3 class="section-title" style="font-size: 1rem;">
              Hosting &amp; ops
            </h3>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-500/50 bg-slate-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Vercel (hosting, SSL, CDN)
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-500/50 bg-slate-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Environment configs via `dotenv`
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-500/50 bg-slate-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Git + CI deploys
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
            The site is deployed from Git pushes; environment variables control local vs. cloud database connections.
          </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section-tight" style="padding-top: 0;">
        <h2 class="section-eyebrow">Why this stack</h2>
        <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          <p class="body-text-small">
            The goal is to keep Palchat easy to maintain: static-first pages, a single database, and well-supported tools.
          </p>
          <ul class="body-text-small" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
            <li style="display: flex; gap: var(--sp-2); margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);">
              <span
                style="margin-top: 6px; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-primary); flex-shrink: 0;"
              />
              <span><span style="font-weight: 500;">Fast by default</span> — most content is static, so pages are quick to load globally.</span>
            </li>
            <li style="display: flex; gap: var(--sp-2); margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);">
              <span
                style="margin-top: 6px; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-primary); flex-shrink: 0;"
              />
              <span><span style="font-weight: 500;">Small moving parts</span> — only a handful of serverless functions and one database.</span>
            </li>
            <li style="display: flex; gap: var(--sp-2);">
              <span
                style="margin-top: 6px; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-primary); flex-shrink: 0;"
              />
              <span><span style="font-weight: 500;">Room to grow</span> — new tools can be added as self-contained pages using the same stack.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
